<Layout title="Wealth Managers · Florida Wealth Manager Partner Hub — HNW Multi-Family Office, Private Bank, Trust Services, Asset-Depletion Qualifying, SBLOC Financing &amp; 2026 Estate Sunset Coordination" description="Florida wealth manager partner hub educating HNW and UHNW buyers on what wealth managers do in real estate transactions: managed AUM verification for Asset-Depletion mortgage qualifying under Fannie Mae B3-3.1-09 asset-based income and Non-QM Asset-Depletion variants converting liquid managed portfolio balance to implied monthly income amortized over 360 months; Securities-Backed Lines of Credit SBLOC or Pledged Asset Line PAL financing through the wealth manager's custodial relationship at Schwab Pledged Asset Line, Fidelity Securities-Backed Line, Goldman Sachs Private Banking, JPMorgan Private Bank, Morgan Stanley Liquidity Access as alternative to mortgage for liquidity-driven HNW buyers avoiding capital gain tax realization on appreciated securities; trust ownership coordination for primary residence with Florida-homestead-compliant revocable trust structures under Florida Statutes Chapter 736 Florida Trust Code; multi-asset class portfolio composition including public equity US large/mid/small cap and international developed and emerging markets plus fixed income treasuries munis corporates high yield plus alternative investments private equity hedge funds private credit real estate funds plus direct real estate plus art and collectibles plus precious metals; family limited partnership FLP or limited liability company LLC ownership structures for asset protection; estate planning coordination given the 2026 federal estate exemption sunset from $13.99M (2025) to approximately $7M per person absent Congressional extension creating substantial gifting and trust funding urgency for dynasty trusts GRATs Grantor Retained Annuity Trusts CLATs Charitable Lead Annuity Trusts QPRTs Qualified Personal Residence Trusts SLATs Spousal Lifetime Access Trusts; concierge family office services spanning tax + insurance + philanthropic (Donor-Advised Funds + private foundations + Charitable Remainder Trusts) + multi-generational continuity planning; and Florida domicile establishment coordination for clients relocating from California, New York, Illinois, or New Jersey. Five wealth manager types: Multi-Family Office MFO serving multiple HNW + UHNW families at $25M+ AUM threshold (Bessemer Trust, Pathstone, Stonehage Fleming, Pitcairn, Cresset Capital); Single-Family Office SFO serving one UHNW family exclusively at $100M+ AUM typical; private bank wealth management at JPMorgan Private Bank, Goldman Sachs Private Wealth, Morgan Stanley Private Wealth Management, UBS Wealth Management, Bank of America Private Bank, Northern Trust, BNY Mellon Wealth Management; boutique RIA wealth manager operating under Investment Advisers Act of 1940 fiduciary standard; trust company wealth manager providing trust services + investment management integrated. Wealth manager designations: CFA Chartered Financial Analyst through CFA Institute; CFP through CFP Board; CPWA Certified Private Wealth Advisor through Investments and Wealth Institute; CIMA Certified Investment Management Analyst; CTFA Certified Trust and Financial Advisor through ABA Trust School; AEP Accredited Estate Planner; Series 65 or 66 or 7 regulatory licenses. Great Wealth Transfer projected at approximately $84 trillion over 25 years 2021-2045 with Florida as primary destination state for transferred wealth. PE consolidator wave reshaping RIA wealth management at 8-12x annual recurring revenue valuations. Partner-as-borrower CTAs routing RIA principals to dedicated mortgage guide with Form 1084 cash-flow addbacks under B3-3.4-02 partnership documentation, and private bank wealth managers to /professional-services/ hub for multi-source variable income under B3-3.1-01." canonical="https://stairwaymortgage.com/wealth-managers/">
